value.name: python - Seconds since date (not epoch!) to date - Stack Overflow
value.snippet: Here t0 is set to a datetime object representing the "epoch" of 1981-01-01. This is your reference datetime to which you can add a timedelta object initialised with an arbitrary number of seconds. The result is a datetime object representing the required date time.
